category.title: category
category.desc: Returns the `category` if it has been set.

name.title: name
name.desc: Returns the `name` if it has been set.

title.title: title
title.desc: Returns properties.title  aka <title> of the page.

referrer.title: referrer
referrer.desc: Returns the `properties.referrer` and falls back on `context.referrer.url`.

properties(aliases).title: properties(aliases)
properties(aliases).desc: Returns all the properties , including the top level name and category. You can also pass an optional object defining aliases.

fullName.title: fullName
fullName.desc: Returns a string that includes both `category` and `name`. Returns only `name` if category is not defined.

event(name).title: event(name)
event(name).desc: Returns `Viewed <name> Page`  if `name` is defined, otherwise returns `Loaded a Page`.

track.title: track
track.desc: Need to quickly convert this call into a `Track` message? This will return a `Track` facade object where the event `name` is the `.event(name)` of the page call.
track.output: Returns a '.track()' facade object where event is 'Viewed Teemo Page' and has all the properties of the page call such as 'title', 'url', 'path', etc.
